Package: accessibletablesR
Type: Package
Title: Creating accessible tables in an Excel workbook
Version: 0.1.0
Author: person("Matthew", "Minifie", email = "matthew.minifie@ons.gov.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Creates Excel spreadsheets which align as closely as possible to UK 
    Government Statistical Service's accessibility criteria. Relies upon the R 
    package "openxlsx". Alternative options include the R package "a11ytables" 
    and the Python package "gptables".
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.3)
Imports:
    tidyverse (>= 1.3.2),
    openxlsx (>= 4.2.5.2)
